<TITLE> 3 cases filed in Sylhet over mutiny </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, May 18 (bdnews24.com)Sylhet police on Sunday filed three treason cases involving BDR sector headquarters, Sylhet and 38 and 8 Rifles Battalions in connection with the Feb 25-26 mutiny. Sylhet Kotwali police chief Syeduzzaman filed the cases with chief metropolitan magistrate TM Musa's court. The court ordered police to investigate the allegations against 100 BDR men. Ahsan Habib Palash, deputy commissioner (north and south), Sylhet Metropolitan Police, confirmed the filing of the cases on Sunday night. A court source requesting anonymity said the rebel border guards have been accused of being involved in anti-state conspiracy, breaking into armoury and looting arms, shooting, arson and stealing valuables from officers' quarters. The court ordered SMP commissioner to complete the primary investigation of the case and submit report by May 26. 
